title: Carbon Emissions by city, United Kingdom, 2006
name: Carbon Emissions by city, United Kingdom, 2006
description: Association of Public Health Observatories publishes data on the total end user CO2 emissions per capita (tonnes of CO2 per resident). Carbon dioxide emission is one of the main contributors to greenhouse gases which cause global warming. If carbon dioxide emissions are not reduced and global warming continues on its present track then there will be serious consequences for health on a world wide scale due among other reasons to reduced ability to produce food, flooding by sea of low lying land and increased frequency of severe weather events. We have to think globally and act locally. While the individual contribution to global carbon dioxide emissions of an individual local authority is negligible, unless all take steps to reduce their carbon dioxide emissions, global warming will continue. This indicator allows local authorities to monitor the effectiveness of their efforts to reduce carbon dioxide emissions.
